Troubleshooting Common Issues
Issue 1: User Namespace Configuration Problems
If user namespaces fail to enable:

# Check kernel support
cat /proc/sys/user/max_user_namespaces

# Verify subuid/subgid configuration
cat /etc/subuid
cat /etc/subgid

# Reset Docker daemon
sudo systemctl stop docker
sudo rm -rf /var/lib/docker
sudo systemctl start docker
Issue 2: Trivy Scanning Errors
If vulnerability scanning fails:

# Update Trivy database
trivy image --download-db-only

# Clear cache and retry
trivy clean --all
trivy image nginx:latest
Issue 3: Container Runtime Issues
If containers fail to start with security features:

# Check AppArmor status
sudo aa-status

# Verify seccomp support
grep CONFIG_SECCOMP /boot/config-$(uname -r)

# Test with minimal security
docker run --rm --security-opt seccomp=unconfined ubuntu:20.04 echo "test"
